### ✅ Mark a Notification as Read (Requires Auth Token)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/notifications/replace_with_notification_id/read
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpZCI6IjY3ZTA1Y2U3N2RjZDI2ZjE4YTQzYTU0YSIsImlhdCI6MTc0Mjc1ODQ1OSwiZXhwIjoxNzQzMzYzMjU5fQ.Ud2xBi7Qsw7tMFBKrMlXHXM4Ro0azNmKcH_ycj3sYEg

###

### ✅ Clear All Notifications (Requires Auth Token)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/notifications/clear
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpZCI6IjY3ZTA1Y2U3N2RjZDI2ZjE4YTQzYTU0YSIsImlhdCI6MTc0Mjc1ODQ1OSwiZXhwIjoxNzQzMzYzMjU5fQ.Ud2xBi7Qsw7tMFBKrMlXHXM4Ro0azNmKcH_ycj3sYEg

###

### ℹ️ Notes:
# - Replace `replace_with_notification_id` with an actual notification ID from your database.
# - You can reuse the token until it expires.
# - Make sure your server is running on port 4000 or update the URL accordingly.
